model.name: Brown et al 2008 Purkinje 1D_1D PIP2_fits 3D model that uses constructed 3D geometry

body.p: 1D models (1 physiological biomodel with two different applications determined by the length of dendritic segment spanning the stimulated spine in respective 3D geometries) for PIP2 concentration changes with stimulated synthesis and lateral diffusion of PIP2. The 1D model geometry uses half of 300um long dendritic branch, represented by a 150um long straight line. Thus, a small length representing half of a dendritic segment spanning the stimulated spine is used for the constructed geometry (0.5 * (1/14 = 0.02714) = 0.0367) and for the experimentally derived geometry (0.5 * (1/11 = 0.0909) = 0.0454). Brown et al 2008 Biophysical Journal
